<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-07T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-07T13:00:00-05:00" n="610" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">865.24B/3–746: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Key</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-07T19:00:00+01:00">March 7, 1946—7
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 8—10:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1210. Within framework of US plans for future of Italian Air Force
                                (see cable from Military Attaché<note n="30" xml:id="d610fn30">Col.
                                    John M. Willems.</note> here to War Department Mar No. 84 dated
                                12 February 1946<note n="31" xml:id="d610fn31">Not found in
                                    Department files.</note>) Embassy supports MA’s (Military
                                Attaché’s) view that US position in Italy would be strengthened by
                                using surplus US aviation equipment at present available in European
                                Theater to equip Italian Air Forces.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Key</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>